# QA After Every Change

Run these checks after **any** substantive edit before marking a task done.

Refer to `.cursor/rules/development-principles.mdc` for full architectural guidance and `.cursor/rules/coding-standards.mdc` for code-level rules.

## 1. ESLint (includes SonarJS rules)
```bash
pnpm lint
```
Zero warnings allowed for `sonarjs/*` rules. Fix all reported issues.

## 2. TypeScript
```bash
pnpm tsc --noEmit
```
Zero type errors allowed.

## 3. SonarCloud Standards Checklist

Refer to `.cursor/rules/coding-standards.mdc` for full guidance. Quick checklist:

- [ ] No function exceeds Cognitive Complexity 15
- [ ] No `parseInt` / `parseFloat` / `isNaN` / `isFinite` (use `Number.*`)
- [ ] No double-prefixed `Number.Number.*` after automated find-replace fixes
- [ ] No `x && x.y` patterns (use `x?.y`)
- [ ] No array index keys in React lists
- [ ] All prop interfaces have `readonly` modifiers
- [ ] No helper functions defined inside React component bodies
- [ ] Interactive elements use `<button>`, not `<div onClick>`
- [ ] No nested ternary expressions ‚Äî use early returns or lookup maps
- [ ] All `.replace(str)` and `.replace(/regex/g)` calls use `.replaceAll()` instead
- [ ] `<html>` root elements include `lang` attribute (e.g. `lang="en"`)
- [ ] `<label>` elements are associated with a control via `htmlFor`, wrapping, or `aria-labelledby`

## 4. Build (for API route changes)
```bash
pnpm build
```

## 5. Database (after schema changes)
```bash
pnpm db:push
```

## 6. Architecture & Code Quality

- [ ] Each file has one clear responsibility ‚Äî no mixing of HTTP handling, business logic, and DB access
- [ ] No duplicate logic ‚Äî shared code lives in `src/lib/`
- [ ] No hardcoded business values ‚Äî rates, limits, roles, and messages use config or env vars
- [ ] No unused imports, commented-out code, or `console.log` left in committed files
- [ ] Country-specific rules go through `CountryRuleSet` / `ConfigValue` DB tables, not `if (country === 'SA')` in code

## 7. Performance

- [ ] No N+1 queries ‚Äî related data is fetched with Prisma `include`, not in a loop
- [ ] List endpoints accept `page` / `limit` params and never return unbounded result sets
- [ ] New Prisma models include `@@index` on all foreign keys and filtered fields
- [ ] `Promise.all` used where multiple async operations are independent

## 8. Security Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded connection strings, passwords, or API keys in any `.ts` / `.tsx` / `.js` file
- [ ] No `?? 'postgresql://...'` or `?? 'sk-...'` fallbacks ‚Äî use `throw new Error(...)` if env var is missing
- [ ] `.env.local` is listed in `.gitignore` and is NOT staged for commit (`git status` must not show it)
- [ ] New secrets are documented in `.env.example` with placeholder values only (e.g. `YOUR_SECRET_HERE`)
- [ ] If a secret was accidentally committed: rotate it in the service dashboard before pushing the fix
- [ ] No overlapping quantifiers in email/domain regex ‚Äî domain group must use `[a-zA-Z0-9-]+(?:\.[a-zA-Z0-9-]+)+`, not `[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\.`
- [ ] No `[\s\S]*` or `[^]*` inside a pattern applied to external/AI input ‚Äî use `indexOf`/`lastIndexOf` for JSON extraction
- [ ] No `^x+|x+$` alternation regex for trimming AI/external output ‚Äî use a string-walk helper (e.g. `stripBackticks`)
- [ ] Every API route validates request body with Zod `safeParse` before touching the database
- [ ] Every API route checks `supabase.auth.getUser()` and `profile.organizationId`
- [ ] Every Prisma query on multi-tenant models includes `organizationId` in `where`
- [ ] No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with unsanitized user or AI content

## 9. Error Handling & Logging

- [ ] Every API route has a `try/catch` returning via the `error()` helper ‚Äî no raw stack traces to clients
- [ ] Server errors use `logger.error` / `logger.warn` from `src/lib/errors/logger.ts`
- [ ] Business events (create, update, delete) call `logActivity` from `src/lib/system-log.ts`

## 10. Documentation (for new features)

- [ ] New environment variables are documented in `.env.example` with a description comment
- [ ] New Prisma models have a comment explaining their purpose
- [ ] New API routes have an inline comment documenting accepted request shape and response shape
- [ ] `README.md` is updated if install, run, or deploy steps changed
